.TH "ti_clk_register_omap_hw" 9 "ti_clk_register_omap_hw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_clk_register_omap_hw \- register a clk_hw_omap to the clock framework
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct clk *" ti_clk_register_omap_hw
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct clk_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "const char *con "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for this clock
.IP "hw" 12
hardware clock handle
.IP "con" 12
connection ID for this clock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Registers a clk_hw_omap clock to the clock framewor, adds a clock alias
for it, and adds the list to the available clk_hw_omap type clocks.
Returns a handle to the registered clock if successful, ERR_PTR value
in failure.
